248 NTSTATUS
249 MiZeroPageFileFirstPage (
250  IN PFILE_OBJECT File
251  )
252 
253 /*++
254 
255 Routine Description:
256 
257  This routine zeroes the first page of the newly created paging file
258  to ensure no stale crashdump signatures get to live on.
259 
260 Arguments:
261 
262  File - Supplies a pointer to the file object for the paging file.
263 
264 Return Value:
265 
266  NTSTATUS.
267 
268 --*/
269 
270 {
271  PMDL Mdl;
272  LARGE_INTEGER Offset = {0};
273  PULONG Block;
274  IO_STATUS_BLOCK IoStatus;
275  NTSTATUS Status;
276  PPFN_NUMBER Page;
277  PFN_NUMBER MdlHack[(sizeof(MDL)/sizeof(PFN_NUMBER)) + 1];
278  KEVENT Event;
279 
280  Mdl = (PMDL)&MdlHack[0];
281 
282  MmCreateMdl (Mdl, NULL, PAGE_SIZE);
283 
284  Mdl->MdlFlags |= MDL_PAGES_LOCKED;
285 
286  Page = (PPFN_NUMBER)(Mdl + 1);
287 
288  *Page = MiGetPageForHeader (FALSE);
289 
290  Block = MmGetSystemAddressForMdlSafe (Mdl, HighPagePriority);
291 
292  if (Block != NULL) {
293  KeZeroSinglePage (Block);
294  }
295  else {
296  MiZeroPhysicalPage (*Page);
297  }
298 
299  KeInitializeEvent (&Event, NotificationEvent, FALSE);
300 
301  Status = IoSynchronousPageWrite (File,
302  Mdl,
303  &Offset,
304  &Event,
305  &IoStatus);
306 
307  if (NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
308 
309  KeWaitForSingleObject (&Event,
310  WrVirtualMemory,
311  KernelMode,
312  FALSE,
313  NULL);
314 
315  Status = IoStatus.Status;
316  }
317 
318  if (Mdl->MdlFlags & MDL_MAPPED_TO_SYSTEM_VA) {
319  MmUnmapLockedPages (Mdl->MappedSystemVa, Mdl);
320  }
321 
322  MiRemoveImageHeaderPage (*Page);
323 
324  return Status;
325 }

328 NTSTATUS
329 NtCreatePagingFile (
330  __in PUNICODE_STRING PageFileName,
331  __in PLARGE_INTEGER MinimumSize,
332  __in PLARGE_INTEGER MaximumSize,
333  __in ULONG Priority
334  )
335 
336 /*++
337 
338 Routine Description:
339 
340  This routine opens the specified file, attempts to write a page
341  to the specified file, and creates the necessary structures to
342  use the file as a paging file.
343 
344  If this file is the first paging file, the modified page writer
345  is started.
346 
347  This system service requires the caller to have SeCreatePagefilePrivilege.
348 
349 Arguments:
350 
351  PageFileName - Supplies the fully qualified file name.
352 
353  MinimumSize - Supplies the starting size of the paging file.
354  This value is rounded up to the host page size.
355 
356  MaximumSize - Supplies the maximum number of bytes to write to the file.
357  This value is rounded up to the host page size.
358 
359  Priority - Supplies the relative priority of this paging file.
360 
361 --*/
362 
363 {
364  ULONG i;
365  PFILE_OBJECT File;
366  NTSTATUS Status;
367  OBJECT_ATTRIBUTES PagingFileAttributes;
368  HANDLE FileHandle;
369  IO_STATUS_BLOCK IoStatus;
370  UNICODE_STRING CapturedName;
371  PWSTR CapturedBuffer;
372  LARGE_INTEGER CapturedMaximumSize;
373  LARGE_INTEGER CapturedMinimumSize;
374  FILE_END_OF_FILE_INFORMATION EndOfFileInformation;
375  KPROCESSOR_MODE PreviousMode;
376  FILE_FS_DEVICE_INFORMATION FileDeviceInfo;
377  ULONG ReturnedLength;
378  ULONG PageFileNumber;
379  ULONG NewMaxSizeInPages;
380  ULONG NewMinSizeInPages;
381  PMMPAGING_FILE FoundExisting;
382  PMMPAGING_FILE NewPagingFile;
383  PRTL_BITMAP NewBitmap;
384  PDEVICE_OBJECT deviceObject;
385  MMPAGE_FILE_EXPANSION PageExtend;
386  SECURITY_DESCRIPTOR SecurityDescriptor;
387  ULONG DaclLength;
388  PACL Dacl;
389 
390 
391  DBG_UNREFERENCED_PARAMETER (Priority);
392 
393  PAGED_CODE();
394 
395  CapturedBuffer = NULL;
396  Dacl = NULL;
397 
398  if (MmNumberOfPagingFiles == MAX_PAGE_FILES) {
399 
400  //
401  // The maximum number of paging files is already in use.
402  //
403 
404  return STATUS_TOO_MANY_PAGING_FILES;
405  }
406 
407  PreviousMode = KeGetPreviousMode();
408 
409  if (PreviousMode != KernelMode) {
410 
411  //
412  // Make sure the caller has the proper privilege for this.
413  //
414 
415  if (!SeSinglePrivilegeCheck (SeCreatePagefilePrivilege, PreviousMode)) {
416  return STATUS_PRIVILEGE_NOT_HELD;
417  }
418 
419  //
420  // Probe arguments.
421  //
422 
423  try {
424 
425 #if !defined (_WIN64)
426 
427  //
428  // Note we only probe for byte alignment because early releases
429  // of NT did and we don't want to break user apps
430  // that had bad alignment if they worked before.
431  //
432 
433  ProbeForReadSmallStructure (PageFileName,
434  sizeof(*PageFileName),
435  sizeof(UCHAR));
436 #else
437  ProbeForReadSmallStructure (PageFileName,
438  sizeof(*PageFileName),
439  PROBE_ALIGNMENT (UNICODE_STRING));
440 #endif
441 
442  ProbeForReadSmallStructure (MaximumSize,
443  sizeof(LARGE_INTEGER),
444  PROBE_ALIGNMENT (LARGE_INTEGER));
445 
446  ProbeForReadSmallStructure (MinimumSize,
447  sizeof(LARGE_INTEGER),
448  PROBE_ALIGNMENT (LARGE_INTEGER));
449 
450  //
451  // Capture arguments.
452  //
453 
454  CapturedMinimumSize = *MinimumSize;
455 
456  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
457 
458  //
459  // If an exception occurs during the probe or capture
460  // of the initial values, then handle the exception and
461  // return the exception code as the status value.
462  //
463 
464  return GetExceptionCode();
465  }
466  }
467  else {
468 
469  //
470  // Capture arguments.
471  //
472 
473  CapturedMinimumSize = *MinimumSize;
474  }
475 
476  if ((CapturedMinimumSize.QuadPart > MI_MAXIMUM_PAGEFILE_SIZE) ||
477  (CapturedMinimumSize.LowPart < MINIMUM_PAGE_FILE_SIZE)) {
478  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER_2;
479  }
480 
481  if (PreviousMode != KernelMode) {
482 
483  try {
484  CapturedMaximumSize = *MaximumSize;
485  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
486 
487  //
488  // If an exception occurs during the probe or capture
489  // of the initial values, then handle the exception and
490  // return the exception code as the status value.
491  //
492 
493  return GetExceptionCode();
494  }
495  }
496  else {
497  CapturedMaximumSize = *MaximumSize;
498  }
499 
500  if (CapturedMaximumSize.QuadPart > MI_MAXIMUM_PAGEFILE_SIZE) {
501  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER_3;
502  }
503 
504  if (CapturedMinimumSize.QuadPart > CapturedMaximumSize.QuadPart) {
505  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER_3;
506  }
507 
508  if (PreviousMode != KernelMode) {
509  try {
510  CapturedName = *PageFileName;
511  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
512 
513  //
514  // If an exception occurs during the probe or capture
515  // of the initial values, then handle the exception and
516  // return the exception code as the status value.
517  //
518 
519  return GetExceptionCode();
520  }
521  }
522  else {
523  CapturedName = *PageFileName;
524  }
525 
526  CapturedName.MaximumLength = CapturedName.Length;
527 
528  if ((CapturedName.Length == 0) ||
529  (CapturedName.Length > MAXIMUM_FILENAME_LENGTH )) {
530  return STATUS_OBJECT_NAME_INVALID;
531  }
532 
533  CapturedBuffer = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (PagedPool,
534  (ULONG)CapturedName.Length,
535  ' mM');
536 
537  if (CapturedBuffer == NULL) {
538  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
539  }
540 
541  if (PreviousMode != KernelMode) {
542  try {
543 
544  ProbeForRead (CapturedName.Buffer,
545  CapturedName.Length,
546  sizeof (UCHAR));
547 
548  //
549  // Copy the string to the allocated buffer.
550  //
551 
552  RtlCopyMemory (CapturedBuffer,
553  CapturedName.Buffer,
554  CapturedName.Length);
555 
556  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
557 
558  //
559  // If an exception occurs during the probe or capture
560  // of the initial values, then handle the exception and
561  // return the exception code as the status value.
562  //
563 
564  ExFreePool (CapturedBuffer);
565 
566  return GetExceptionCode();
567  }
568  }
569  else {
570 
571  //
572  // Copy the string to the allocated buffer.
573  //
574 
575  RtlCopyMemory (CapturedBuffer,
576  CapturedName.Buffer,
577  CapturedName.Length);
578  }
579 
580  //
581  // Point the buffer to the string that was just copied.
582  //
583 
584  CapturedName.Buffer = CapturedBuffer;
585 
586  //
587  // Create a security descriptor to protect the pagefile
588  //
589  Status = RtlCreateSecurityDescriptor (&SecurityDescriptor,
590  SECURITY_DESCRIPTOR_REVISION);
591 
592  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
593  goto ErrorReturn1;
594  }
595  DaclLength = sizeof (ACL) + sizeof (ACCESS_ALLOWED_ACE) * 2 +
596  RtlLengthSid (SeLocalSystemSid) +
597  RtlLengthSid (SeAliasAdminsSid);
598 
599  Dacl = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (PagedPool, DaclLength, 'lcaD');
600 
601  if (Dacl == NULL) {
602  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
603  goto ErrorReturn1;
604  }
605 
606  Status = RtlCreateAcl (Dacl, DaclLength, ACL_REVISION);
607 
608  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
609  goto ErrorReturn1;
610  }
611 
612  Status = RtlAddAccessAllowedAce (Dacl,
613  ACL_REVISION,
614  FILE_ALL_ACCESS,
615  SeAliasAdminsSid);
616 
617  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
618  goto ErrorReturn1;
619  }
620 
621  Status = RtlAddAccessAllowedAce (Dacl,
622  ACL_REVISION,
623  FILE_ALL_ACCESS,
624  SeLocalSystemSid);
625 
626  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
627  goto ErrorReturn1;
628  }
629 
630  Status = RtlSetDaclSecurityDescriptor (&SecurityDescriptor,
631  TRUE,
632  Dacl,
633  FALSE);
634 
635  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
636  goto ErrorReturn1;
637  }
638 
639 
640  //
641  // Open a paging file and get the size.
642  //
643 
644  InitializeObjectAttributes (&PagingFileAttributes,
645  &CapturedName,
646  (OBJ_CASE_INSENSITIVE | OBJ_KERNEL_HANDLE),
647  NULL,
648  &SecurityDescriptor);
649 
650 //
651 // Note this macro cannot use ULONG_PTR as it must also work on PAE.
652 //
653 
654 #define ROUND64_TO_PAGES(Size) (((ULONG64)(Size) + PAGE_SIZE - 1) & ~(PAGE_SIZE - 1))
655 
656  EndOfFileInformation.EndOfFile.QuadPart =
657  ROUND64_TO_PAGES (CapturedMinimumSize.QuadPart);
658 
659  Status = IoCreateFile (&FileHandle,
660  FILE_READ_DATA | FILE_WRITE_DATA | WRITE_DAC | SYNCHRONIZE,
661  &PagingFileAttributes,
662  &IoStatus,
663  &CapturedMinimumSize,
664  FILE_ATTRIBUTE_HIDDEN | FILE_ATTRIBUTE_SYSTEM,
665  FILE_SHARE_WRITE,
666  FILE_SUPERSEDE,
667  FILE_NO_INTERMEDIATE_BUFFERING | FILE_NO_COMPRESSION | FILE_DELETE_ON_CLOSE,
668  NULL,
669  0L,
670  CreateFileTypeNone,
671  NULL,
672  IO_OPEN_PAGING_FILE | IO_NO_PARAMETER_CHECKING);
673 
674  if (NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
675 
676  //
677  // Update the DACL in case there was a pre-existing regular file named
678  // pagefile.sys (even supersede above does not do this).
679  //
680 
681  if (NT_SUCCESS(IoStatus.Status)) {
682 
683  Status = ZwSetSecurityObject (FileHandle,
684  DACL_SECURITY_INFORMATION,
685  &SecurityDescriptor);
686 
687  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
688  goto ErrorReturn2;
689  }
690  }
691  }
692  else {
693 
694  //
695  // Treat this as an extension of an existing pagefile maximum -
696  // and try to open rather than create the paging file specified.
697  //
698 
699  Status = IoCreateFile (&FileHandle,
700  FILE_WRITE_DATA | SYNCHRONIZE,
701  &PagingFileAttributes,
702  &IoStatus,
703  &CapturedMinimumSize,
704  FILE_ATTRIBUTE_HIDDEN | FILE_ATTRIBUTE_SYSTEM,
705  FILE_SHARE_READ | FILE_SHARE_WRITE,
706  FILE_OPEN,
707  FILE_NO_INTERMEDIATE_BUFFERING | FILE_NO_COMPRESSION,
708  (PVOID) NULL,
709  0L,
710  CreateFileTypeNone,
711  (PVOID) NULL,
712  IO_OPEN_PAGING_FILE | IO_NO_PARAMETER_CHECKING);
713 
714  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
715 
716 #if DBG
717  if (Status != STATUS_DISK_FULL) {
718  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_INFO_LEVEL,
719  "MM MODWRITE: unable to open paging file %wZ - status = %X \n", &CapturedName, Status);
720  }
721 #endif
722 
723  goto ErrorReturn1;
724  }
725 
726  Status = ObReferenceObjectByHandle (FileHandle,
727  FILE_READ_DATA | FILE_WRITE_DATA,
728  IoFileObjectType,
729  KernelMode,
730  (PVOID *)&File,
731  NULL);
732 
733  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
734  goto ErrorReturn2;
735  }
736 
737  FoundExisting = NULL;
738 
739  KeAcquireGuardedMutex (&MmPageFileCreationLock);
740 
741  for (PageFileNumber = 0; PageFileNumber < MmNumberOfPagingFiles; PageFileNumber += 1) {
742  if (MmPagingFile[PageFileNumber]->File->SectionObjectPointer == File->SectionObjectPointer) {
743  FoundExisting = MmPagingFile[PageFileNumber];
744  break;
745  }
746  }
747 
748  if (FoundExisting == NULL) {
749  Status = STATUS_NOT_FOUND;
750  goto ErrorReturn4;
751  }
752 
753  //
754  // Check for increases in the minimum or the maximum paging file sizes.
755  // Decreasing either paging file size on the fly is not allowed.
756  //
757 
758  NewMaxSizeInPages = (ULONG)(CapturedMaximumSize.QuadPart >> PAGE_SHIFT);
759  NewMinSizeInPages = (ULONG)(CapturedMinimumSize.QuadPart >> PAGE_SHIFT);
760 
761  if (FoundExisting->MinimumSize > NewMinSizeInPages) {
762  Status = STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER_2;
763  goto ErrorReturn4;
764  }
765 
766  if (FoundExisting->MaximumSize > NewMaxSizeInPages) {
767  Status = STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER_3;
768  goto ErrorReturn4;
769  }
770 
771  if (NewMaxSizeInPages > FoundExisting->MaximumSize) {
772 
773  //
774  // Make sure that the pagefile increase doesn't cause the commit
775  // limit (in pages) to wrap. Currently this can only happen on
776  // PAE systems where 16 pagefiles of 16TB (==256TB) is greater
777  // than the 32-bit commit variable (max is 16TB).
778  //
779 
780  if (MmTotalCommitLimitMaximum + (NewMaxSizeInPages - FoundExisting->MaximumSize) <= MmTotalCommitLimitMaximum) {
781  Status = STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER_3;
782  goto ErrorReturn4;
783  }
784 
785  //
786  // Handle the increase to the maximum paging file size.
787  //
788 
789  MiCreateBitMap (&NewBitmap, NewMaxSizeInPages, NonPagedPool);
790 
791  if (NewBitmap == NULL) {
792  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
793  goto ErrorReturn4;
794  }
795 
796  MiExtendPagingFileMaximum (PageFileNumber, NewBitmap);
797 
798  //
799  // We may be low on commitment and/or may have put a temporary
800  // stopgate on things. Clear up the logjam now by forcing an
801  // extension and immediately returning it.
802  //
803 
804  if (MmTotalCommittedPages + 100 > MmTotalCommitLimit) {
805  if (MiChargeCommitment (200, NULL) == TRUE) {
806  MiReturnCommitment (200);
807  }
808  }
809  }
810 
811  if (NewMinSizeInPages > FoundExisting->MinimumSize) {
812 
813  //
814  // Handle the increase to the minimum paging file size.
815  //
816 
817  if (NewMinSizeInPages > FoundExisting->Size) {
818 
819  //
820  // Queue a message to the segment dereferencing / pagefile
821  // extending thread to see if the page file can be extended.
822  //
823 
824  PageExtend.InProgress = 1;
825  PageExtend.ActualExpansion = 0;
826  PageExtend.RequestedExpansionSize = NewMinSizeInPages - FoundExisting->Size;
827  PageExtend.Segment = NULL;
828  PageExtend.PageFileNumber = PageFileNumber;
829  KeInitializeEvent (&PageExtend.Event, NotificationEvent, FALSE);
830 
831  MiIssuePageExtendRequest (&PageExtend);
832  }
833 
834  //
835  // The current size is now greater than the new desired minimum.
836  // Ensure subsequent contractions obey this new minimum.
837  //
838 
839  if (FoundExisting->Size >= NewMinSizeInPages) {
840  ASSERT (FoundExisting->Size >= FoundExisting->MinimumSize);
841  ASSERT (NewMinSizeInPages >= FoundExisting->MinimumSize);
842  FoundExisting->MinimumSize = NewMinSizeInPages;
843  }
844  else {
845 
846  //
847  // The pagefile could not be expanded to handle the new minimum.
848  // No easy way to undo any maximum raising that may have been
849  // done as the space may have already been used, so just set
850  // Status so our caller knows it didn't all go perfectly.
851  //
852 
853  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
854  }
855  }
856 
857  goto ErrorReturn4;
858  }
859 
860  //
861  // Free the DACL as it's no longer needed.
862  //
863 
864  ExFreePool (Dacl);
865  Dacl = NULL;
866 
867  if (!NT_SUCCESS(IoStatus.Status)) {
868  KdPrint(("MM MODWRITE: unable to open paging file %wZ - iosb %lx\n", &CapturedName, IoStatus.Status));
869  Status = IoStatus.Status;
870  goto ErrorReturn1;
871  }
872 
873  //
874  // Make sure that the pagefile increase doesn't cause the commit
875  // limit (in pages) to wrap. Currently this can only happen on
876  // PAE systems where 16 pagefiles of 16TB (==256TB) is greater
877  // than the 32-bit commit variable (max is 16TB).
878  //
879 
880  if (MmTotalCommitLimitMaximum + (CapturedMaximumSize.QuadPart >> PAGE_SHIFT)
881  <= MmTotalCommitLimitMaximum) {
882  Status = STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER_3;
883  goto ErrorReturn2;
884  }
885 
886  Status = ZwSetInformationFile (FileHandle,
887  &IoStatus,
888  &EndOfFileInformation,
889  sizeof(EndOfFileInformation),
890  FileEndOfFileInformation);
891 
892  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
893  KdPrint(("MM MODWRITE: unable to set length of paging file %wZ status = %X \n",
894  &CapturedName, Status));
895  goto ErrorReturn2;
896  }
897 
898  if (!NT_SUCCESS(IoStatus.Status)) {
899  KdPrint(("MM MODWRITE: unable to set length of paging file %wZ - iosb %lx\n",
900  &CapturedName, IoStatus.Status));
901  Status = IoStatus.Status;
902  goto ErrorReturn2;
903  }
904 
905  Status = ObReferenceObjectByHandle ( FileHandle,
906  FILE_READ_DATA | FILE_WRITE_DATA,
907  IoFileObjectType,
908  KernelMode,
909  (PVOID *)&File,
910  NULL );
911 
912  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
913  KdPrint(("MM MODWRITE: Unable to reference paging file - %wZ\n",
914  &CapturedName));
915  goto ErrorReturn2;
916  }
917 
918  //
919  // Get the address of the target device object and ensure
920  // the specified file is of a suitable type.
921  //
922 
923  deviceObject = IoGetRelatedDeviceObject (File);
924 
925  if ((deviceObject->DeviceType != FILE_DEVICE_DISK_FILE_SYSTEM) &&
926  (deviceObject->DeviceType != FILE_DEVICE_NETWORK_FILE_SYSTEM) &&
927  (deviceObject->DeviceType != FILE_DEVICE_DFS_VOLUME) &&
928  (deviceObject->DeviceType != FILE_DEVICE_DFS_FILE_SYSTEM)) {
929  KdPrint(("MM MODWRITE: Invalid paging file type - %x\n",
930  deviceObject->DeviceType));
931  Status = STATUS_UNRECOGNIZED_VOLUME;
932  goto ErrorReturn3;
933  }
934 
935  //
936  // Make sure the specified file is not currently being used
937  // as a mapped data file.
938  //
939 
940  Status = MiCheckPageFileMapping (File);
941  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
942  goto ErrorReturn3;
943  }
944 
945  //
946  // Make sure the volume is not a floppy disk.
947  //
948 
949  Status = IoQueryVolumeInformation ( File,
950  FileFsDeviceInformation,
951  sizeof(FILE_FS_DEVICE_INFORMATION),
952  &FileDeviceInfo,
953  &ReturnedLength
954  );
955 
956  if (FILE_FLOPPY_DISKETTE & FileDeviceInfo.Characteristics) {
957  Status = STATUS_FLOPPY_VOLUME;
958  goto ErrorReturn3;
959  }
960 
961  //
962  // Check with all of the drivers along the path to the file to ensure
963  // that they are willing to follow the rules required of them and to
964  // give them a chance to lock down code and data that needs to be locked.
965  // If any of the drivers along the path refuses to participate, fail the
966  // pagefile creation.
967  //
968 
969  Status = PpPagePathAssign (File);
970 
971  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
972  KdPrint(( "PpPagePathAssign(%wZ) FAILED: %x\n", &CapturedName, Status ));
973  //
974  // Fail the pagefile creation if the storage stack tells us to.
975  //
976 
977  goto ErrorReturn3;
978  }
979 
980  NewPagingFile = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
981  sizeof(MMPAGING_FILE),
982  ' mM');
983 
984  if (NewPagingFile == NULL) {
985 
986  //
987  // Allocate pool failed.
988  //
989 
990  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
991  goto ErrorReturn3;
992  }
993 
994  RtlZeroMemory (NewPagingFile, sizeof(MMPAGING_FILE));
995 
996  NewPagingFile->File = File;
997  NewPagingFile->FileHandle = FileHandle;
998  NewPagingFile->Size = (PFN_NUMBER)(CapturedMinimumSize.QuadPart >> PAGE_SHIFT);
999  NewPagingFile->MinimumSize = NewPagingFile->Size;
1000  NewPagingFile->FreeSpace = NewPagingFile->Size - 1;
1001 
1002  NewPagingFile->MaximumSize = (PFN_NUMBER)(CapturedMaximumSize.QuadPart >>
1003  PAGE_SHIFT);
1004 
1005  for (i = 0; i < MM_PAGING_FILE_MDLS; i += 1) {
1006 
1007  NewPagingFile->Entry[i] = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
1008  sizeof(MMMOD_WRITER_MDL_ENTRY) +
1009  MmModifiedWriteClusterSize *
1010  sizeof(PFN_NUMBER),
1011  ' mM');
1012 
1013  if (NewPagingFile->Entry[i] == NULL) {
1014 
1015  //
1016  // Allocate pool failed.
1017  //
1018 
1019  while (i != 0) {
1020  i -= 1;
1021  ExFreePool (NewPagingFile->Entry[i]);
1022  }
1023 
1024  ExFreePool (NewPagingFile);
1025  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
1026  goto ErrorReturn3;
1027  }
1028 
1029  RtlZeroMemory (NewPagingFile->Entry[i], sizeof(MMMOD_WRITER_MDL_ENTRY));
1030 
1031  NewPagingFile->Entry[i]->PagingListHead = &MmPagingFileHeader;
1032 
1033  NewPagingFile->Entry[i]->PagingFile = NewPagingFile;
1034  }
1035 
1036  NewPagingFile->PageFileName = CapturedName;
1037 
1038  MiCreateBitMap (&NewPagingFile->Bitmap,
1039  NewPagingFile->MaximumSize,
1040  NonPagedPool);
1041 
1042  if (NewPagingFile->Bitmap == NULL) {
1043 
1044  //
1045  // Allocate pool failed.
1046  //
1047 
1048  ExFreePool (NewPagingFile->Entry[0]);
1049  ExFreePool (NewPagingFile->Entry[1]);
1050  ExFreePool (NewPagingFile);
1051  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
1052  goto ErrorReturn3;
1053  }
1054 
1055  Status = MiZeroPageFileFirstPage (File);
1056 
1057  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
1058 
1059  //
1060  // The storage stack could not zero the first page of the file.
1061  // This means an old crashdump signature could still be around so
1062  // fail the create.
1063  //
1064 
1065  for (i = 0; i < MM_PAGING_FILE_MDLS; i += 1) {
1066  ExFreePool (NewPagingFile->Entry[i]);
1067  }
1068  ExFreePool (NewPagingFile);
1069  MiRemoveBitMap (&NewPagingFile->Bitmap);
1070  goto ErrorReturn3;
1071  }
1072 
1073  RtlSetAllBits (NewPagingFile->Bitmap);
1074 
1075  //
1076  // Set the first bit as 0 is an invalid page location, clear the
1077  // following bits.
1078  //
1079 
1080  RtlClearBits (NewPagingFile->Bitmap,
1081  1,
1082  (ULONG)(NewPagingFile->Size - 1));
1083 
1084  //
1085  // See if this pagefile is on the boot partition, and if so, mark it
1086  // so we can find it later if someone enables crashdump.
1087  //
1088 
1089  if (File->DeviceObject->Flags & DO_SYSTEM_BOOT_PARTITION) {
1090  NewPagingFile->BootPartition = 1;
1091  }
1092  else {
1093  NewPagingFile->BootPartition = 0;
1094  }
1095 
1096  //
1097  // Acquire the global page file creation mutex.
1098  //
1099 
1100  KeAcquireGuardedMutex (&MmPageFileCreationLock);
1101 
1102  PageFileNumber = MmNumberOfPagingFiles;
1103 
1104  MmPagingFile[PageFileNumber] = NewPagingFile;
1105 
1106  NewPagingFile->PageFileNumber = PageFileNumber;
1107 
1108  MiInsertPageFileInList ();
1109 
1110  if (PageFileNumber == 0) {
1111 
1112  //
1113  // The first paging file has been created and reservation of any
1114  // crashdump pages has completed, signal the modified
1115  // page writer.
1116  //
1117 
1118  MiReleaseModifiedWriter ();
1119  }
1120 
1121  KeReleaseGuardedMutex (&MmPageFileCreationLock);
1122 
1123  //
1124  // Note that the file handle (a kernel handle) is not closed during the
1125  // create path (it IS duped and closed in the pagefile size extending path)
1126  // to prevent the paging file from being deleted or opened again. It is
1127  // also kept open so that extensions of existing pagefiles can be detected
1128  // because successive IoCreateFile calls will fail.
1129  //
1130 
1131  if ((!MmSystemPageFileLocated) &&
1132  (File->DeviceObject->Flags & DO_SYSTEM_BOOT_PARTITION)) {
1133  MmSystemPageFileLocated = IoInitializeCrashDump (FileHandle);
1134  }
1135 
1136  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
1137 
1138  //
1139  // Error returns:
1140  //
1141 
1142 ErrorReturn4:
1143  KeReleaseGuardedMutex (&MmPageFileCreationLock);
1144 
1145 ErrorReturn3:
1146  ObDereferenceObject (File);
1147 
1148 ErrorReturn2:
1149  ZwClose (FileHandle);
1150 
1151 ErrorReturn1:
1152  if (Dacl != NULL) {
1153  ExFreePool (Dacl);
1154  }
1155 
1156  ExFreePool (CapturedBuffer);
1157 
1158  return Status;
1159 }

1162 HANDLE
1163 MmGetSystemPageFile (
1164  VOID
1165  )
1166 /*++
1167 
1168 Routine Description:
1169 
1170  Returns a filehandle to the paging file on the system boot partition.
1171  This is used by crashdump to enable crashdump after the system has
1172  already booted.
1173 
1174 Arguments:
1175 
1176  None.
1177 
1178 Return Value:
1179 
1180  A file handle to the paging file on the system boot partition,
1181  NULL if no such pagefile exists.
1182 
1183 --*/
1184 
1185 {
1186  HANDLE FileHandle;
1187  ULONG PageFileNumber;
1188 
1189  PAGED_CODE();
1190 
1191  FileHandle = NULL;
1192 
1193  KeAcquireGuardedMutex (&MmPageFileCreationLock);
1194  for (PageFileNumber = 0; PageFileNumber < MmNumberOfPagingFiles; PageFileNumber += 1) {
1195  if (MmPagingFile[PageFileNumber]->BootPartition) {
1196  FileHandle = MmPagingFile[PageFileNumber]->FileHandle;
1197  }
1198  }
1199  KeReleaseGuardedMutex (&MmPageFileCreationLock);
1200 
1201  return FileHandle;
1202 }

1205 LOGICAL
1206 MmIsFileObjectAPagingFile (
1207  IN PFILE_OBJECT FileObject
1208  )
1209 /*++
1210 
1211 Routine Description:
1212 
1213  Returns TRUE if the file object refers to a paging file, FALSE if not.
1214 
1215 Arguments:
1216 
1217  FileObject - Supplies the file object in question.
1218 
1219 Return Value:
1220 
1221  Returns TRUE if the file object refers to a paging file, FALSE if not.
1222 
1223  Note this routine is called both at DISPATCH_LEVEL by drivers in their
1224  completion routines and it is called in the path to satisfy pagefile reads,
1225  so it cannot be made pageable.
1226 
1227 --*/
1228 
1229 {
1230  PMMPAGING_FILE PageFile;
1231  PMMPAGING_FILE *PagingFile;
1232  PMMPAGING_FILE *PagingFileEnd;
1233 
1234  //
1235  // It's ok to check without synchronization.
1236  //
1237 
1238  PagingFile = MmPagingFile;
1239  PagingFileEnd = PagingFile + MmNumberOfPagingFiles;
1240 
1241  while (PagingFile < PagingFileEnd) {
1242  PageFile = *PagingFile;
1243  if (PageFile->File == FileObject) {
1244  return TRUE;
1245  }
1246  PagingFile += 1;
1247  }
1248 
1249  return FALSE;
1250 }

1253 VOID
1254 MiExtendPagingFileMaximum (
1255  IN ULONG PageFileNumber,
1256  IN PRTL_BITMAP NewBitmap
1257  )
1258 
1259 /*++
1260 
1261 Routine Description:
1262 
1263  This routine switches from the old bitmap to the new (larger) bitmap.
1264 
1265 Arguments:
1266 
1267  PageFileNumber - Supplies the paging file number to be extended.
1268 
1269  NewBitmap - Supplies the new bitmap to use.
1270 
1271 Return Value:
1272 
1273  Returns a non-NULL value for the caller to free to pool
1274 
1275 Environment:
1276 
1277  Kernel mode, APC_LEVEL, MmPageFileCreationLock held.
1278 
1279 --*/
1280 
1281 {
1282  KIRQL OldIrql;
1283  PRTL_BITMAP OldBitmap;
1284  SIZE_T Delta;
1285 
1286  OldBitmap = MmPagingFile[PageFileNumber]->Bitmap;
1287 
1288  RtlSetAllBits (NewBitmap);
1289 
1290  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
1291 
1292  //
1293  // Copy the bits from the existing map.
1294  //
1295 
1296  RtlCopyMemory (NewBitmap->Buffer,
1297  OldBitmap->Buffer,
1298  ((OldBitmap->SizeOfBitMap + 31) / 32) * sizeof (ULONG));
1299 
1300  Delta = NewBitmap->SizeOfBitMap - OldBitmap->SizeOfBitMap;
1301 
1302  InterlockedExchangeAddSizeT (&MmTotalCommitLimitMaximum, Delta);
1303 
1304  MmPagingFile[PageFileNumber]->MaximumSize = NewBitmap->SizeOfBitMap;
1305 
1306  MmPagingFile[PageFileNumber]->Bitmap = NewBitmap;
1307 
1308  //
1309  // If any MDLs are waiting for space, get them up now.
1310  //
1311 
1312  if (!IsListEmpty (&MmFreePagingSpaceLow)) {
1313  MiUpdateModifiedWriterMdls (PageFileNumber);
1314  }
1315 
1316  //
1317  // The modified writer may be scanning the old map without holding any
1318  // locks - if so, he will have reference counted the old bitmap, so only
1319  // free it if this isn't in progress. If it is in progress, the modified
1320  // writer will free the old bitmap.
1321  //
1322 
1323  if (MmPagingFile[PageFileNumber]->ReferenceCount != 0) {
1324  ASSERT (MmPagingFile[PageFileNumber]->ReferenceCount == 1);
1325  OldBitmap = NULL;
1326  }
1327 
1328  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
1329 
1330  if (OldBitmap != NULL) {
1331  MiRemoveBitMap (&OldBitmap);
1332  }
1333 }

1336 VOID
1337 MiFinishPageFileExtension (
1338  IN ULONG PageFileNumber,
1339  IN PFN_NUMBER AdditionalAllocation
1340  )
1341 
1342 /*++
1343 
1344 Routine Description:
1345 
1346  This routine finishes the specified page file extension.
1347 
1348 Arguments:
1349 
1350  PageFileNumber - Supplies the page file number to attempt to extend.
1351 
1352  SizeNeeded - Supplies the number of pages to extend the file by.
1353 
1354  Maximum - Supplies TRUE if the page file should be extended
1355  by the maximum size possible, but not to exceed
1356  SizeNeeded.
1357 
1358 Return Value:
1359 
1360  None.
1361 
1362 --*/
1363 
1364 {
1365  KIRQL OldIrql;
1366  PMMPAGING_FILE PagingFile;
1367 
1368  //
1369  // Clear bits within the paging file bitmap to allow the extension
1370  // to take effect.
1371  //
1372 
1373  PagingFile = MmPagingFile[PageFileNumber];
1374 
1375  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
1376 
1377  ASSERT (RtlCheckBit (PagingFile->Bitmap, (ULONG) PagingFile->Size) == 1);
1378 
1379  RtlClearBits (PagingFile->Bitmap,
1380  (ULONG)PagingFile->Size,
1381  (ULONG)AdditionalAllocation);
1382 
1383  PagingFile->Size += AdditionalAllocation;
1384  PagingFile->FreeSpace += AdditionalAllocation;
1385 
1386  MiUpdateModifiedWriterMdls (PageFileNumber);
1387 
1388  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
1389 
1390  return;
1391 }

1394 SIZE_T
1395 MiAttemptPageFileExtension (
1396  IN ULONG PageFileNumber,
1397  IN SIZE_T SizeNeeded,
1398  IN LOGICAL Maximum
1399  )
1400 
1401 /*++
1402 
1403 Routine Description:
1404 
1405  This routine attempts to extend the specified page file by SizeNeeded.
1406 
1407 Arguments:
1408 
1409  PageFileNumber - Supplies the page file number to attempt to extend.
1410 
1411  SizeNeeded - Supplies the number of pages to extend the file by.
1412 
1413  Maximum - Supplies TRUE if the page file should be extended
1414  by the maximum size possible, but not to exceed
1415  SizeNeeded.
1416 
1417 Return Value:
1418 
1419  Returns the size of the extension. Zero if the page file cannot
1420  be extended.
1421 
1422 --*/
1423 
1424 {
1425 
1426  NTSTATUS status;
1427  FILE_FS_SIZE_INFORMATION FileInfo;
1428  FILE_END_OF_FILE_INFORMATION EndOfFileInformation;
1429  ULONG AllocSize;
1430  ULONG ReturnedLength;
1431  PFN_NUMBER PagesAvailable;
1432  SIZE_T SizeToExtend;
1433  SIZE_T MinimumExtension;
1434  LARGE_INTEGER BytesAvailable;
1435 
1436  //
1437  // Check to see if this page file is at the maximum.
1438  //
1439 
1440  if (MmPagingFile[PageFileNumber]->Size ==
1441  MmPagingFile[PageFileNumber]->MaximumSize) {
1442  return 0;
1443  }
1444 
1445  //
1446  // Find out how much free space is on this volume.
1447  //
1448 
1449  status = IoQueryVolumeInformation (MmPagingFile[PageFileNumber]->File,
1450  FileFsSizeInformation,
1451  sizeof(FileInfo),
1452  &FileInfo,
1453  &ReturnedLength);
1454 
1455  if (!NT_SUCCESS (status)) {
1456 
1457  //
1458  // The volume query did not succeed - return 0 indicating
1459  // the paging file was not extended.
1460  //
1461 
1462  return 0;
1463  }
1464 
1465  //
1466  // Attempt to extend by at least 16 megabytes, if that fails then attempt
1467  // for at least a megabyte.
1468  //
1469 
1470  MinimumExtension = MmPageFileExtension << 4;
1471 
1472 retry:
1473 
1474  SizeToExtend = SizeNeeded;
1475 
1476  if (SizeNeeded < MinimumExtension) {
1477  SizeToExtend = MinimumExtension;
1478  }
1479  else {
1480  MinimumExtension = MmPageFileExtension;
1481  }
1482 
1483  //
1484  // Don't go over the maximum size for the paging file.
1485  //
1486 
1487  ASSERT (MmPagingFile[PageFileNumber]->MaximumSize >= MmPagingFile[PageFileNumber]->Size);
1488 
1489  PagesAvailable = MmPagingFile[PageFileNumber]->MaximumSize -
1490  MmPagingFile[PageFileNumber]->Size;
1491 
1492  if (SizeToExtend > PagesAvailable) {
1493  SizeToExtend = PagesAvailable;
1494 
1495  if ((SizeToExtend < SizeNeeded) && (Maximum == FALSE)) {
1496 
1497  //
1498  // Can't meet the requested (mandatory) requirement.
1499  //
1500 
1501  return 0;
1502  }
1503  }
1504 
1505  //
1506  // See if there is enough space on the volume for the extension.
1507  //
1508 
1509  AllocSize = FileInfo.SectorsPerAllocationUnit * FileInfo.BytesPerSector;
1510 
1511  BytesAvailable = RtlExtendedIntegerMultiply (
1512  FileInfo.AvailableAllocationUnits,
1513  AllocSize);
1514 
1515  if ((UINT64)BytesAvailable.QuadPart > (UINT64)MmMinimumFreeDiskSpace) {
1516 
1517  BytesAvailable.QuadPart = BytesAvailable.QuadPart -
1518  (LONGLONG)MmMinimumFreeDiskSpace;
1519 
1520  if ((UINT64)BytesAvailable.QuadPart > (((UINT64)SizeToExtend) << PAGE_SHIFT)) {
1521  BytesAvailable.QuadPart = (((LONGLONG)SizeToExtend) << PAGE_SHIFT);
1522  }
1523 
1524  PagesAvailable = (PFN_NUMBER)(BytesAvailable.QuadPart >> PAGE_SHIFT);
1525 
1526  if ((Maximum == FALSE) && (PagesAvailable < SizeNeeded)) {
1527 
1528  //
1529  // Can't meet the requested (mandatory) requirement.
1530  //
1531 
1532  return 0;
1533  }
1534 
1535  }
1536  else {
1537 
1538  //
1539  // Not enough space is available period.
1540  //
1541 
1542  return 0;
1543  }
1544 
1545 #if defined (_WIN64) || defined (_X86PAE_)
1546  EndOfFileInformation.EndOfFile.QuadPart =
1547  ((ULONG64)MmPagingFile[PageFileNumber]->Size + PagesAvailable) * PAGE_SIZE;
1548 #else
1549  EndOfFileInformation.EndOfFile.LowPart =
1550  (MmPagingFile[PageFileNumber]->Size + PagesAvailable) * PAGE_SIZE;
1551 
1552  //
1553  // Set high part to zero as paging files are limited to 4GB.
1554  //
1555 
1556  EndOfFileInformation.EndOfFile.HighPart = 0;
1557 #endif
1558 
1559  //
1560  // Attempt to extend the file by setting the end-of-file position.
1561  //
1562 
1563  ASSERT (KeGetCurrentIrql() < DISPATCH_LEVEL);
1564 
1565  status = IoSetInformation (MmPagingFile[PageFileNumber]->File,
1566  FileEndOfFileInformation,
1567  sizeof(FILE_END_OF_FILE_INFORMATION),
1568  &EndOfFileInformation);
1569 
1570  if (status != STATUS_SUCCESS) {
1571  KdPrint(("MM MODWRITE: page file extension failed %p %lx\n",PagesAvailable,status));
1572 
1573  if (MinimumExtension != MmPageFileExtension) {
1574  MinimumExtension = MmPageFileExtension;
1575  goto retry;
1576  }
1577 
1578  return 0;
1579  }
1580 
1581  MiFinishPageFileExtension (PageFileNumber, PagesAvailable);
1582 
1583  return PagesAvailable;
1584 }
1585 
1586 SIZE_T
1587 MiExtendPagingFiles (
1588  IN PMMPAGE_FILE_EXPANSION PageExpand
1589  )
1590 
1591 /*++
1592 
1593 Routine Description:
1594 
1595  This routine attempts to extend the paging files to provide
1596  SizeNeeded bytes.
1597 
1598  Note - Page file expansion and page file reduction are synchronized
1599  because a single thread is responsible for performing the
1600  operation. Hence, while expansion is occurring, a reduction
1601  request will be queued to the thread.
1602 
1603 Arguments:
1604 
1605  PageFileNumber - Supplies the page file number to extend.
1606  MI_EXTEND_ANY_PAGFILE indicates to extend any page file.
1607 
1608 Return Value:
1609 
1610  Returns the size of the extension. Zero if the page file(s) cannot
1611  be extended.
1612 
1613 --*/
1614 
1615 {
1616  SIZE_T DesiredQuota;
1617  ULONG PageFileNumber;
1618  SIZE_T ExtendedSize;
1619  SIZE_T SizeNeeded;
1620  ULONG i;
1621  SIZE_T CommitLimit;
1622  SIZE_T CommittedPages;
1623 
1624  DesiredQuota = PageExpand->RequestedExpansionSize;
1625  PageFileNumber = PageExpand->PageFileNumber;
1626 
1627  ASSERT (PageExpand->ActualExpansion == 0);
1628 
1629  ASSERT (PageFileNumber < MmNumberOfPagingFiles || PageFileNumber == MI_EXTEND_ANY_PAGEFILE);
1630 
1631  if (MmNumberOfPagingFiles == 0) {
1632  InterlockedExchange ((PLONG)&PageExpand->InProgress, 0);
1633  return 0;
1634  }
1635 
1636  if (PageFileNumber < MmNumberOfPagingFiles) {
1637  i = PageFileNumber;
1638  ExtendedSize = MmPagingFile[i]->MaximumSize - MmPagingFile[i]->Size;
1639  if (ExtendedSize < DesiredQuota) {
1640  InterlockedExchange ((PLONG)&PageExpand->InProgress, 0);
1641  return 0;
1642  }
1643 
1644  ExtendedSize = MiAttemptPageFileExtension (i, DesiredQuota, FALSE);
1645  goto alldone;
1646  }
1647 
1648  //
1649  // Snap the globals into locals so calculations will be consistent from
1650  // step to step. It is ok to snap the globals unsynchronized with respect
1651  // to each other as even when pagefile expansion occurs, the expansion
1652  // space is not reserved for the caller - any process could consume
1653  // the expansion prior to this routine returning.
1654  //
1655 
1656  CommittedPages = MmTotalCommittedPages;
1657  CommitLimit = MmTotalCommitLimit;
1658 
1659  SizeNeeded = CommittedPages + DesiredQuota + MmSystemCommitReserve;
1660 
1661  //
1662  // Check to make sure the request does not wrap.
1663  //
1664 
1665  if (SizeNeeded < CommittedPages) {
1666  InterlockedExchange ((PLONG)&PageExpand->InProgress, 0);
1667  return 0;
1668  }
1669 
1670  //
1671  // Check to see if ample space already exists.
1672  //
1673 
1674  if (SizeNeeded <= CommitLimit) {
1675  PageExpand->ActualExpansion = 1;
1676  InterlockedExchange ((PLONG)&PageExpand->InProgress, 0);
1677  return 1;
1678  }
1679 
1680  //
1681  // Calculate the additional pages needed.
1682  //
1683 
1684  SizeNeeded -= CommitLimit;
1685  if (SizeNeeded > MmSystemCommitReserve) {
1686  SizeNeeded -= MmSystemCommitReserve;
1687  }
1688 
1689  //
1690  // Make sure ample space exists within the paging files.
1691  //
1692 
1693  i = 0;
1694  ExtendedSize = 0;
1695 
1696  do {
1697  ExtendedSize += MmPagingFile[i]->MaximumSize - MmPagingFile[i]->Size;
1698  i += 1;
1699  } while (i < MmNumberOfPagingFiles);
1700 
1701  if (ExtendedSize < SizeNeeded) {
1702  InterlockedExchange ((PLONG)&PageExpand->InProgress, 0);
1703  return 0;
1704  }
1705 
1706  //
1707  // Attempt to extend only one of the paging files.
1708  //
1709 
1710  i = 0;
1711  do {
1712  ExtendedSize = MiAttemptPageFileExtension (i, SizeNeeded, FALSE);
1713  if (ExtendedSize != 0) {
1714  goto alldone;
1715  }
1716  i += 1;
1717  } while (i < MmNumberOfPagingFiles);
1718 
1719  ASSERT (ExtendedSize == 0);
1720 
1721  if (MmNumberOfPagingFiles == 1) {
1722 
1723  //
1724  // If the attempt didn't succeed for one (not enough disk space free) -
1725  // don't try to set it to the maximum size.
1726  //
1727 
1728  InterlockedExchange ((PLONG)&PageExpand->InProgress, 0);
1729  return 0;
1730  }
1731 
1732  //
1733  // Attempt to extend all paging files.
1734  //
1735 
1736  i = 0;
1737  do {
1738  ASSERT (SizeNeeded > ExtendedSize);
1739  ExtendedSize += MiAttemptPageFileExtension (i,
1740  SizeNeeded - ExtendedSize,
1741  TRUE);
1742  if (ExtendedSize >= SizeNeeded) {
1743  goto alldone;
1744  }
1745  i += 1;
1746  } while (i < MmNumberOfPagingFiles);
1747 
1748  //
1749  // Not enough space is available.
1750  //
1751 
1752  InterlockedExchange ((PLONG)&PageExpand->InProgress, 0);
1753  return 0;
1754 
1755 alldone:
1756 
1757  ASSERT (ExtendedSize != 0);
1758 
1759  PageExpand->ActualExpansion = ExtendedSize;
1760 
1761  //
1762  // Increase the systemwide commit limit.
1763  //
1764 
1765  InterlockedExchangeAddSizeT (&MmTotalCommitLimit, ExtendedSize);
1766 
1767  //
1768  // Clear the in progress flag - if this is the global cantexpand structure
1769  // it is possible for it to be immediately reused.
1770  //
1771 
1772  InterlockedExchange ((PLONG)&PageExpand->InProgress, 0);
1773 
1774  return ExtendedSize;
1775 }
1776 
1777 MMPAGE_FILE_EXPANSION MiPageFileContract;
1778 
1779 
1780 VOID
1781 MiContractPagingFiles (
1782  VOID
1783  )
1784 
1785 /*++
1786 
1787 Routine Description:
1788 
1789  This routine checks to see if ample space is no longer committed
1790  and if so, does enough free space exist in any paging file.
1791 
1792  IFF the answer to both these is affirmative, a reduction in the
1793  paging file size(s) is attempted.
1794 
1795 Arguments:
1796 
1797  None.
1798 
1799 Return Value:
1800 
1801  None.
1802 
1803 --*/
1804 
1805 {
1806  ULONG i;
1807  KIRQL OldIrql;
1808  PMMPAGE_FILE_EXPANSION PageReduce;
1809 
1810  //
1811  // This is an unsynchronized check but that's ok. The real check is
1812  // made when the packet below is processed by the dereference thread.
1813  //
1814 
1815  if (MmTotalCommittedPages >= ((MmTotalCommitLimit/10)*8)) {
1816  return;
1817  }
1818 
1819  if ((MmTotalCommitLimit - MmMinimumPageFileReduction) <=
1820  MmTotalCommittedPages) {
1821  return;
1822  }
1823 
1824  for (i = 0; i < MmNumberOfPagingFiles; i += 1) {
1825  if (MmPagingFile[i]->Size != MmPagingFile[i]->MinimumSize) {
1826  if (MmPagingFile[i]->FreeSpace > MmMinimumPageFileReduction) {
1827  break;
1828  }
1829  }
1830  }
1831 
1832  if (i == MmNumberOfPagingFiles) {
1833  return;
1834  }
1835 
1836  PageReduce = &MiPageFileContract;
1837 
1838  //
1839  // See if the page file contraction item is already queued up, if so then
1840  // nothing more needs to be done.
1841  //
1842 
1843  ExAcquireSpinLock (&MmDereferenceSegmentHeader.Lock, &OldIrql);
1844 
1845  if (PageReduce->RequestedExpansionSize == MI_CONTRACT_PAGEFILES) {
1846 
1847  ExReleaseSpinLock (&MmDereferenceSegmentHeader.Lock, OldIrql);
1848 
1849  return;
1850  }
1851 
1852  PageReduce->Segment = NULL;
1853  PageReduce->RequestedExpansionSize = MI_CONTRACT_PAGEFILES;
1854 
1855  InsertTailList (&MmDereferenceSegmentHeader.ListHead,
1856  &PageReduce->DereferenceList);
1857 
1858  ExReleaseSpinLock (&MmDereferenceSegmentHeader.Lock, OldIrql);
1859 
1860  KeReleaseSemaphore (&MmDereferenceSegmentHeader.Semaphore, 0L, 1L, FALSE);
1861  return;
1862 }
1863 
1864 VOID
1865 MiAttemptPageFileReduction (
1866  VOID
1867  )
1868 
1869 /*++
1870 
1871 Routine Description:
1872 
1873  This routine attempts to reduce the size of the paging files to
1874  their minimum levels.
1875 
1876  Note - Page file expansion and page file reduction are synchronized
1877  because a single thread is responsible for performing the
1878  operation. Hence, while expansion is occurring, a reduction
1879  request will be queued to the thread.
1880 
1881 Arguments:
1882 
1883  None.
1884 
1885 Return Value:
1886 
1887  None.
1888 
1889 --*/
1890 
1891 {
1892  SIZE_T CommitLimit;
1893  SIZE_T CommittedPages;
1894  SIZE_T SafetyMargin;
1895  KIRQL OldIrql;
1896  ULONG i;
1897  ULONG j;
1898  PFN_NUMBER StartReduction;
1899  PFN_NUMBER ReductionSize;
1900  PFN_NUMBER TryBit;
1901  PFN_NUMBER TryReduction;
1902  PMMPAGING_FILE PagingFile;
1903  SIZE_T MaxReduce;
1904  FILE_ALLOCATION_INFORMATION FileAllocationInfo;
1905  NTSTATUS status;
1906 
1907  //
1908  // Mark the global pagefile contraction item as being processed so other
1909  // threads will know to reset it if another contraction is desired.
1910  //
1911 
1912  ExAcquireSpinLock (&MmDereferenceSegmentHeader.Lock, &OldIrql);
1913 
1914  ASSERT (MiPageFileContract.RequestedExpansionSize == MI_CONTRACT_PAGEFILES);
1915 
1916  MiPageFileContract.RequestedExpansionSize = ~MI_CONTRACT_PAGEFILES;
1917 
1918  ExReleaseSpinLock (&MmDereferenceSegmentHeader.Lock, OldIrql);
1919 
1920  //
1921  // Snap the globals into locals so calculations will be consistent from
1922  // step to step. It is ok to snap the globals unsynchronized with respect
1923  // to each other.
1924  //
1925 
1926  CommittedPages = MmTotalCommittedPages;
1927  CommitLimit = MmTotalCommitLimit;
1928 
1929  //
1930  // Make sure the commit limit is significantly greater than the number
1931  // of committed pages to avoid thrashing.
1932  //
1933 
1934  SafetyMargin = 2 * MmMinimumPageFileReduction;
1935 
1936  if (CommittedPages + SafetyMargin >= ((CommitLimit/10)*8)) {
1937  return;
1938  }
1939 
1940  MaxReduce = ((CommitLimit/10)*8) - (CommittedPages + SafetyMargin);
1941 
1942  ASSERT ((SSIZE_T)MaxReduce > 0);
1943  ASSERT ((LONG_PTR)MaxReduce >= 0);
1944 
1945  for (i = 0; i < MmNumberOfPagingFiles; i += 1) {
1946 
1947  if (MaxReduce < MmMinimumPageFileReduction) {
1948 
1949  //
1950  // Don't reduce any more paging files.
1951  //
1952 
1953  break;
1954  }
1955 
1956  PagingFile = MmPagingFile[i];
1957 
1958  if (PagingFile->Size == PagingFile->MinimumSize) {
1959  continue;
1960  }
1961 
1962  //
1963  // This unsynchronized check is ok because a synchronized check is
1964  // made later.
1965  //
1966 
1967  if (PagingFile->FreeSpace < MmMinimumPageFileReduction) {
1968  continue;
1969  }
1970 
1971  //
1972  // Lock the PFN database and check to see if ample pages
1973  // are free at the end of the paging file.
1974  //
1975 
1976  TryBit = PagingFile->Size - MmMinimumPageFileReduction;
1977  TryReduction = MmMinimumPageFileReduction;
1978 
1979  if (TryBit <= PagingFile->MinimumSize) {
1980  TryBit = PagingFile->MinimumSize;
1981  TryReduction = PagingFile->Size - PagingFile->MinimumSize;
1982  }
1983 
1984  StartReduction = 0;
1985  ReductionSize = 0;
1986 
1987  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
1988 
1989  do {
1990 
1991  //
1992  // Try to reduce.
1993  //
1994 
1995  if ((ReductionSize + TryReduction) > MaxReduce) {
1996 
1997  //
1998  // The reduction attempt would remove more
1999  // than MaxReduce pages.
2000  //
2001 
2002  break;
2003  }
2004 
2005  if (RtlAreBitsClear (PagingFile->Bitmap,
2006  (ULONG)TryBit,
2007  (ULONG)TryReduction)) {
2008 
2009  //
2010  // Can reduce it by TryReduction, see if it can
2011  // be made smaller.
2012  //
2013 
2014  StartReduction = TryBit;
2015  ReductionSize += TryReduction;
2016 
2017  if (StartReduction == PagingFile->MinimumSize) {
2018  break;
2019  }
2020 
2021  TryBit = StartReduction - MmMinimumPageFileReduction;
2022 
2023  if (TryBit <= PagingFile->MinimumSize) {
2024  TryReduction -= PagingFile->MinimumSize - TryBit;
2025  TryBit = PagingFile->MinimumSize;
2026  }
2027  else {
2028  TryReduction = MmMinimumPageFileReduction;
2029  }
2030  }
2031  else {
2032 
2033  //
2034  // Reduction has failed.
2035  //
2036 
2037  break;
2038  }
2039 
2040  } while (TRUE);
2041 
2042  //
2043  // Make sure there are no outstanding writes to
2044  // pages within the start reduction range.
2045  //
2046 
2047  if (StartReduction != 0) {
2048 
2049  //
2050  // There is an outstanding write past where the
2051  // new end of the paging file should be. This
2052  // is a very rare condition, so just punt shrinking
2053  // the file.
2054  //
2055 
2056  for (j = 0; j < MM_PAGING_FILE_MDLS; j += 1) {
2057  if (PagingFile->Entry[j]->LastPageToWrite > StartReduction) {
2058  StartReduction = 0;
2059  break;
2060  }
2061  }
2062  }
2063 
2064  //
2065  // If there are no pages to remove, march on to the next pagefile.
2066  //
2067 
2068  if (StartReduction == 0) {
2069  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
2070  continue;
2071  }
2072 
2073  //
2074  // Reduce the paging file's size and free space.
2075  //
2076 
2077  ASSERT (ReductionSize == (PagingFile->Size - StartReduction));
2078 
2079  PagingFile->Size = StartReduction;
2080  PagingFile->FreeSpace -= ReductionSize;
2081 
2082  RtlSetBits (PagingFile->Bitmap,
2083  (ULONG)StartReduction,
2084  (ULONG)ReductionSize );
2085 
2086  //
2087  // Release the PFN lock now that the size info
2088  // has been updated.
2089  //
2090 
2091  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
2092 
2093  MaxReduce -= ReductionSize;
2094  ASSERT ((LONG)MaxReduce >= 0);
2095 
2096  //
2097  // Change the commit limit to reflect the returned page file space.
2098  // First try to charge the reduction amount to confirm that the
2099  // reduction is still a sensible thing to do.
2100  //
2101 
2102  if (MiChargeTemporaryCommitmentForReduction (ReductionSize + SafetyMargin) == FALSE) {
2103 
2104  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
2105 
2106  PagingFile->Size = StartReduction + ReductionSize;
2107  PagingFile->FreeSpace += ReductionSize;
2108 
2109  RtlClearBits (PagingFile->Bitmap,
2110  (ULONG)StartReduction,
2111  (ULONG)ReductionSize );
2112 
2113  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
2114 
2115  ASSERT ((LONG)(MaxReduce + ReductionSize) >= 0);
2116 
2117  break;
2118  }
2119 
2120  //
2121  // Reduce the systemwide commit limit - note this is carefully done
2122  // *PRIOR* to returning this commitment so no one else (including a DPC
2123  // in this very thread) can consume past the limit.
2124  //
2125 
2126  InterlockedExchangeAddSizeT (&MmTotalCommitLimit, 0 - ReductionSize);
2127 
2128  //
2129  // Now that the systemwide commit limit has been lowered, the amount
2130  // we have removed can be safely returned.
2131  //
2132 
2133  MiReturnCommitment (ReductionSize + SafetyMargin);
2134 
2135 #if defined (_WIN64) || defined (_X86PAE_)
2136  FileAllocationInfo.AllocationSize.QuadPart =
2137  ((ULONG64)StartReduction << PAGE_SHIFT);
2138 
2139 #else
2140  FileAllocationInfo.AllocationSize.LowPart = StartReduction * PAGE_SIZE;
2141 
2142  //
2143  // Set high part to zero, paging files are limited to 4gb.
2144  //
2145 
2146  FileAllocationInfo.AllocationSize.HighPart = 0;
2147 #endif
2148 
2149  //
2150  // Reduce the allocated size of the paging file
2151  // thereby actually freeing the space and
2152  // setting a new end of file.
2153  //
2154 
2155  ASSERT (KeGetCurrentIrql() < DISPATCH_LEVEL);
2156 
2157  status = IoSetInformation (PagingFile->File,
2158  FileAllocationInformation,
2159  sizeof(FILE_ALLOCATION_INFORMATION),
2160  &FileAllocationInfo);
2161 #if DBG
2162  //
2163  // Ignore errors on truncating the paging file
2164  // as we can always have less space in the bitmap
2165  // than the pagefile holds.
2166  //
2167 
2168  if (status != STATUS_SUCCESS) {
2169  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_INFO_LEVEL,
2170  "MM: pagefile truncate status %lx\n", status);
2171  }
2172 #endif
2173  }
2174 
2175  return;
2176 }

2259 VOID
2260 MiWriteComplete (
2261  IN PVOID Context,
2262  IN PIO_STATUS_BLOCK IoStatus,
2263  IN ULONG Reserved
2264  )
2265 
2266 /*++
2267 
2268 Routine Description:
2269 
2270  This routine is the APC write completion procedure. It is invoked
2271  at APC_LEVEL when a page write operation is completed.
2272 
2273 Arguments:
2274 
2275  Context - Supplies a pointer to the MOD_WRITER_MDL_ENTRY which was
2276  used for this I/O.
2277 
2278  IoStatus - Supplies a pointer to the IO_STATUS_BLOCK which was used
2279  for this I/O.
2280 
2281 Return Value:
2282 
2283  None.
2284 
2285 Environment:
2286 
2287  Kernel mode, APC_LEVEL.
2288 
2289 --*/
2290 
2291 {
2292  PKEVENT Event;
2293  LONG ClusterWritesDisabled;
2294  LONG OldClusterWritesDisabled;
2295  PMM_LDW_WORK_CONTEXT LdwContext;
2296  PMMMOD_WRITER_MDL_ENTRY WriterEntry;
2297  PMMMOD_WRITER_MDL_ENTRY NextWriterEntry;
2298  PPFN_NUMBER Page;
2299  PMMPFN Pfn1;
2300  KIRQL OldIrql;
2301  LONG ByteCount;
2302  NTSTATUS status;
2303  PCONTROL_AREA ControlArea;
2304  LOGICAL FailAllIo;
2305  LOGICAL MarkDirty;
2306  PFILE_OBJECT FileObject;
2307  PERESOURCE FileResource;
2308 
2309  UNREFERENCED_PARAMETER (Reserved);
2310 
2311  ASSERT (KeAreAllApcsDisabled () == TRUE);
2312 
2313  Event = NULL;
2314  FailAllIo = FALSE;
2315  MarkDirty = FALSE;
2316 
2317  //
2318  // A page write has completed, at this time the pages are not
2319  // on any lists, write-in-progress is set in the PFN database,
2320  // and the reference count was incremented.
2321  //
2322 
2323  WriterEntry = (PMMMOD_WRITER_MDL_ENTRY)Context;
2324  ByteCount = (LONG) WriterEntry->Mdl.ByteCount;
2325  Page = &WriterEntry->Page[0];
2326 
2327  if (WriterEntry->Mdl.MdlFlags & MDL_MAPPED_TO_SYSTEM_VA) {
2328  MmUnmapLockedPages (WriterEntry->Mdl.MappedSystemVa,
2329  &WriterEntry->Mdl);
2330  }
2331 
2332  status = IoStatus->Status;
2333  ControlArea = WriterEntry->ControlArea;
2334 
2335  //
2336  // Do as much work as possible before acquiring the PFN lock.
2337  //
2338 
2339  while (ByteCount > 0) {
2340 
2341  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (*Page);
2342  *Page = (PFN_NUMBER) Pfn1;
2343  Page += 1;
2344  ByteCount -= (LONG)PAGE_SIZE;
2345  }
2346 
2347  ByteCount = (LONG) WriterEntry->Mdl.ByteCount;
2348  Page = &WriterEntry->Page[0];
2349 
2350  FileResource = WriterEntry->FileResource;
2351 
2352  if (FileResource != NULL) {
2353  FileObject = WriterEntry->File;
2354  FsRtlReleaseFileForModWrite (FileObject, FileResource);
2355  }
2356  else if (ControlArea == NULL) {
2357  LARGE_INTEGER CurrentTime;
2358  KeQuerySystemTime (&CurrentTime);
2359  MI_PAGEFILE_WRITE (WriterEntry, &CurrentTime, 0, status);
2360  }
2361 
2362  if (!NT_SUCCESS (status)) {
2363 
2364  //
2365  // If the file object is over the network, assume that this
2366  // I/O operation can never complete and mark the pages as
2367  // clean and indicate in the control area all I/O should fail.
2368  // Note that the modified bit in the PFN database is not set.
2369  //
2370  // If the user changes the protection on the volume containing the
2371  // file to readonly, this puts us in a problematic situation. We
2372  // cannot just keep retrying the writes because if there are no
2373  // other pages that can be written, not writing these can cause the
2374  // system to run out of pages, ie: bugcheck 4D. So throw away
2375  // these pages just as if they were on a network that has
2376  // disappeared.
2377  //
2378 
2379  if (((status != STATUS_FILE_LOCK_CONFLICT) &&
2380  (ControlArea != NULL) &&
2381  (ControlArea->u.Flags.Networked == 1))
2382  ||
2383  (status == STATUS_FILE_INVALID)
2384  ||
2385  ((status == STATUS_MEDIA_WRITE_PROTECTED) &&
2386  (ControlArea != NULL))) {
2387 
2388  if (ControlArea->u.Flags.FailAllIo == 0) {
2389  ControlArea->u.Flags.FailAllIo = 1;
2390  FailAllIo = TRUE;
2391 
2392  KdPrint(("MM MODWRITE: failing all io, controlarea %p status %lx\n",
2393  ControlArea, status));
2394  }
2395  }
2396  else {
2397 
2398  //
2399  // The modified write operation failed, SET the modified bit
2400  // for each page which was written and free the page file
2401  // space.
2402  //
2403 
2404 #if DBG
2405  ULONG i;
2406 
2407  //
2408  // Save error status information to ease debugging. Since this
2409  // doesn't need to be exact, don't bother lock-synchronizing.
2410  //
2411 
2412  for (i = 0; i < MM_MAX_MODWRITE_ERRORS - 1; i += 1) {
2413

2752 LOGICAL
2753 MiCancelWriteOfMappedPfn (
2754  IN PFN_NUMBER PageToStop,
2755  IN KIRQL OldIrql
2756  )
2757 
2758 /*++
2759 
2760 Routine Description:
2761 
2762  This routine attempts to stop a pending mapped page writer write for the
2763  specified PFN. Note that if the write can be stopped, any other pages
2764  that may be clustered with the write are also stopped.
2765 
2766 Arguments:
2767 
2768  PageToStop - Supplies the frame number that the caller wants to stop.
2769 
2770  OldIrql - Supplies the IRQL the caller acquired the PFN lock at.
2771 
2772 Return Value:
2773 
2774  TRUE if the write was stopped, FALSE if not.
2775 
2776 Environment:
2777 
2778  Kernel mode, PFN lock held. The PFN lock is released and reacquired if
2779  the write was stopped.
2780 
2781  N.B. No other locks may be held as IRQL is lowered to APC_LEVEL here.
2782 
2783 --*/
2784 
2785 {
2786  ULONG i;
2787  ULONG PageCount;
2788  PPFN_NUMBER Page;
2789  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
2790  PMDL MemoryDescriptorList;
2791  PMMMOD_WRITER_MDL_ENTRY ModWriterEntry;
2792 
2793  //
2794  // Walk the MmMappedPageWriterList looking for an MDL which contains
2795  // the argument page. If found, remove it and cancel the write.
2796  //
2797 
2798  NextEntry = MmMappedPageWriterList.Flink;
2799  while (NextEntry != &MmMappedPageWriterList) {
2800 
2801  ModWriterEntry = CONTAINING_RECORD(NextEntry,
2802  MMMOD_WRITER_MDL_ENTRY,
2803  Links);
2804 
2805  MemoryDescriptorList = &ModWriterEntry->Mdl;
2806  PageCount = (MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount >> PAGE_SHIFT);
2807  Page = (PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1);
2808 
2809  for (i = 0; i < PageCount; i += 1) {
2810  if (*Page == PageToStop) {
2811  RemoveEntryList (NextEntry);
2812  goto CancelWrite;
2813  }
2814  Page += 1;
2815  }
2816 
2817  NextEntry = NextEntry->Flink;
2818  }
2819 
2820  return FALSE;
2821 
2822 CancelWrite:
2823 
2824  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
2825 
2826  //
2827  // File lock conflict to indicate an error has occurred,
2828  // but that future I/Os should be allowed. Keep APCs disabled and
2829  // call the write completion routine.
2830  //
2831 
2832  ModWriterEntry->u.IoStatus.Status = STATUS_FILE_LOCK_CONFLICT;
2833  ModWriterEntry->u.IoStatus.Information = 0;
2834 
2835  KeRaiseIrql (APC_LEVEL, &OldIrql);
2836  MiWriteComplete ((PVOID)ModWriterEntry,
2837  &ModWriterEntry->u.IoStatus,
2838  0);

2840 
2841  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);

2860

2900  //
2901

2903

3842 
3843 Routine Description:
3844 
3845  This routine processes the specified modified page by getting
3846  that page and gather any other pages on the modified list destined
3847  for the paging file in a large write cluster. This cluster is
3848  then written to the paging file.
3849 
3850 Arguments:
3851

3861

3890  //

3899  }

4336 MiMappedPageWriter (
4337  IN PVOID StartContext
4338  )
4339 
4340 /*++
4341 
4342 Routine Description:
4343 
4344  Implements the NT secondary modified page writer thread.
4345  Requests for writes to mapped files are sent to this thread.
4346  This is required as the writing of mapped file pages could cause
4347  page faults resulting in requests for free pages. But there
4348  could be no free pages - hence a deadlock. Rather than deadlock
4349  the whole system waiting on the modified page writer, creating
4350  a secondary thread allows that thread to block without affecting
4351  ongoing page file writes.
4352 
4353 Arguments:
4354 
4355  StartContext - not used.
4356 
4357 Return Value:
4358 
4359  None.
4360 
4361 Environment:
4362 
4363  Kernel mode.
4364 
4365 --*/
4366 
4367 {
4368  KIRQL OldIrql;
4369  NTSTATUS Status;
4370  KEVENT TempEvent;
4371  PETHREAD CurrentThread;
4372  IO_PAGING_PRIORITY IrpPriority;
4373  PMMMOD_WRITER_MDL_ENTRY ModWriterEntry;
4374 
4375  UNREFERENCED_PARAMETER (StartContext);
4376 
4377  //
4378  // Make this a real time thread.
4379  //
4380 
4381  CurrentThread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
4382 
4383  KeSetPriorityThread (&CurrentThread->Tcb, LOW_REALTIME_PRIORITY + 1);
4384 
4385  CurrentThread->MemoryMaker = 1;

4388  // Let the file system know that we are getting resources.
4389  //
4390

4392

4394 
4395  while (TRUE) {
4396 
4397  KeWaitForSingleObject (&MmMappedPageWriterEvent,
4398  WrVirtualMemory,
4399  KernelMode,
4400  FALSE,
4401  NULL);
4402 
4403  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4404 
4405  if (IsListEmpty (&MmMappedPageWriterList)) {
4406  KeClearEvent (&MmMappedPageWriterEvent);
4407  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4408  }
4409  else {
4410 
4411  ModWriterEntry = (PMMMOD_WRITER_MDL_ENTRY)RemoveHeadList (
4412  &MmMappedPageWriterList);
4413 
4414  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4415 
4416  if (ModWriterEntry->ControlArea->u.Flags.FailAllIo == 1) {
4417  Status = STATUS_UNSUCCESSFUL;
4418  }
4419  else {
4420  Status = FsRtlAcquireFileForModWriteEx (ModWriterEntry->File,
4421  &ModWriterEntry->u.LastByte,
4422  &ModWriterEntry->FileResource);

4424

4426  // Issue the write request.
4427  //
4428

4435  }
4436  else {
4437  MiMappedWriteBurstCount = 0;

4439  }
4440  else if (MmAvailablePages < MM_HIGH_LIMIT) {
4441  MiMappedWriteBurstCount = MI_MAXIMUM_PRIORITY_BURST;
4442  IrpPriority = IoPagingPriorityHigh;
4443  }

4858 VOID
4859 MiPageFileFull (
4860  VOID
4861  )
4862 
4863 /*++
4864 
4865 Routine Description:
4866 
4867  This routine is called when no space can be found in a paging file.
4868  It looks through all the paging files to see if ample space is
4869  available and if not, tries to expand the paging files.
4870 
4871  If more than 90% of all the paging files are in use, the commitment limit
4872  is set to the total and then 100 pages are added.
4873 
4874 Arguments:
4875 
4876  None.
4877 
4878 Return Value:
4879 
4880  None.
4881 
4882 --*/
4883 
4884 {
4885  ULONG i;
4886  PFN_NUMBER Total;
4887  PFN_NUMBER Free;
4888  SIZE_T QuotaCharge;
4889 
4890  if (MmNumberOfPagingFiles == 0) {
4891  return;
4892  }
4893 
4894  Total = 0;
4895  Free = 0;
4896 
4897  for (i = 0; i < MmNumberOfPagingFiles; i += 1) {
4898  Total += MmPagingFile[i]->Size;
4899  Free += MmPagingFile[i]->FreeSpace;
4900  }
4901 
4902  //
4903  // Check to see if more than 90% of the total space has been used.
4904  //
4905 
4906  if (((Total >> 5) + (Total >> 4)) >= Free) {
4907 
4908  //
4909  // Try to expand the paging files.
4910  //
4911  // Check (unsynchronized is ok) commit limits of each pagefile.
4912  // If all the pagefiles are already at their maximums, then don't
4913  // make things worse by setting commit to the maximum - this gives
4914  // systems with lots of memory a longer lease on life when they have
4915  // small pagefiles.
4916  //
4917 
4918  i = 0;
4919 
4920  do {
4921  if (MmPagingFile[i]->MaximumSize > MmPagingFile[i]->Size) {
4922  break;
4923  }
4924  i += 1;
4925  } while (i < MmNumberOfPagingFiles);
4926 
4927  if (i == MmNumberOfPagingFiles) {
4928 
4929  //
4930  // No pagefiles can be extended,
4931  // display a popup if we haven't before.
4932  //
4933 
4934  MiCauseOverCommitPopup ();
4935 
4936  return;
4937  }
4938 
4939  QuotaCharge = MmTotalCommitLimit - MmTotalCommittedPages;
4940 
4941  //
4942  // IFF the total number of committed pages is less than the limit,
4943  // or in any event, no more than 50 pages past the limit,
4944  // then charge pages against the commitment to trigger pagefile
4945  // expansion.
4946  //
4947  // If the total commit is more than 50 past the limit, then don't
4948  // bother trying to extend the pagefile.
4949  //
4950 
4951  if ((SSIZE_T)QuotaCharge + 50 > 0) {
4952 
4953  if ((SSIZE_T)QuotaCharge < 50) {
4954  QuotaCharge = 50;
4955  }
4956 
4957  MiChargeCommitmentCantExpand (QuotaCharge, TRUE);
4958 
4959  MM_TRACK_COMMIT (MM_DBG_COMMIT_PAGEFILE_FULL, QuotaCharge);
4960 
4961  //
4962  // Display a popup if we haven't before.
4963  //
4964 
4965  MiCauseOverCommitPopup ();
4966 
4967  MiReturnCommitment (QuotaCharge);
4968 
4969  MM_TRACK_COMMIT (MM_DBG_COMMIT_RETURN_PAGEFILE_FULL, QuotaCharge);
4970  }
4971  }
4972  return;
4973 }

5027 LOGICAL
5028 MiIssuePageExtendRequest (
5029  IN PMMPAGE_FILE_EXPANSION PageExtend
5030  )
5031 
5032 /*++
5033 
5034 Routine Description:
5035 
5036  Queue a message to the segment dereferencing / pagefile extending
5037  thread to see if the page file can be extended. Extension is done
5038  in the context of a system thread due to mutexes which the current
5039  thread may be holding.
5040 
5041 Arguments:
5042 
5043  PageExtend - Supplies a pointer to the page file extension request.
5044 
5045 Return Value:
5046 
5047  TRUE indicates the request completed. FALSE indicates the request timed
5048  out and was removed.
5049 
5050 Environment:
5051 
5052  Kernel mode. No locks held. APC_LEVEL or below.
5053 
5054 --*/
5055 
5056 {
5057  ULONG i;
5058  KIRQL OldIrql;
5059  NTSTATUS status;
5060  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
5061  PETHREAD Thread;
5062 
5063  Thread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
5064 
5065  //
5066  // The segment dereference thread cannot wait for itself !
5067  //
5068 
5069  if (Thread->StartAddress == (PVOID)(ULONG_PTR)MiDereferenceSegmentThread) {
5070  return FALSE;
5071  }
5072 
5073  //
5074  // Avoid repeatedly waking the segment dereference thread just for it to
5075  // perform a no-op by first checking whether the pagefile(s) are already
5076  // at their maximum (or don't exist) - if so, just return a failure.
5077  //
5078 
5079  for (i = 0; i < MmNumberOfPagingFiles; i += 1) {
5080  if (MmPagingFile[i]->Size < MmPagingFile[i]->MaximumSize) {
5081  break;
5082  }
5083  }
5084 
5085  if (i == MmNumberOfPagingFiles) {
5086  return FALSE;
5087  }
5088 
5089  ExAcquireSpinLock (&MmDereferenceSegmentHeader.Lock, &OldIrql);
5090 
5091  InsertHeadList (&MmDereferenceSegmentHeader.ListHead,
5092  &PageExtend->DereferenceList);
5093 
5094  ExReleaseSpinLock (&MmDereferenceSegmentHeader.Lock, OldIrql);
5095 
5096  KeReleaseSemaphore (&MmDereferenceSegmentHeader.Semaphore,
5097  0L,
5098  1L,
5099  TRUE);
5100 
5101  //
5102  // Wait for the thread to extend the paging file.
5103  //
5104 
5105  status = KeWaitForSingleObject (&PageExtend->Event,
5106  Executive,
5107  KernelMode,
5108  FALSE,
5109  (PageExtend->RequestedExpansionSize < 10) ?
5110  (PLARGE_INTEGER)&MmOneSecond : (PLARGE_INTEGER)&MmTwentySeconds);
5111 
5112  if (status == STATUS_TIMEOUT) {
5113 
5114  //
5115  // The wait has timed out, if this request has not
5116  // been processed, remove it from the list and check
5117  // to see if we should allow this request to succeed.
5118  // This prevents a deadlock between the file system
5119  // trying to allocate memory in the FSP and the
5120  // segment dereferencing thread trying to close a
5121  // file object, and waiting in the file system.
5122  //
5123 
5124  KdPrint(("MiIssuePageExtendRequest: wait timed out, page-extend= %p, quota = %lx\n",
5125  PageExtend, PageExtend->RequestedExpansionSize));
5126 
5127  ExAcquireSpinLock (&MmDereferenceSegmentHeader.Lock, &OldIrql);
5128 
5129  NextEntry = MmDereferenceSegmentHeader.ListHead.Flink;
5130 
5131  while (NextEntry != &MmDereferenceSegmentHeader.ListHead) {
5132 
5133  //
5134  // Check to see if this is the entry we are waiting for.
5135  //
5136 
5137  if (NextEntry == &PageExtend->DereferenceList) {
5138 
5139  //
5140  // Remove this entry.
5141  //
5142 
5143  RemoveEntryList (&PageExtend->DereferenceList);
5144  ExReleaseSpinLock (&MmDereferenceSegmentHeader.Lock, OldIrql);
5145  return FALSE;
5146  }
5147  NextEntry = NextEntry->Flink;
5148  }
5149 
5150  ExReleaseSpinLock (&MmDereferenceSegmentHeader.Lock, OldIrql);
5151 
5152  //
5153  // Entry is being processed, wait for completion.
5154  //
5155 
5156  KdPrint (("MiIssuePageExtendRequest: rewaiting...\n"));
5157 
5158  KeWaitForSingleObject (&PageExtend->Event,
5159  Executive,
5160  KernelMode,
5161  FALSE,
5162  NULL);
5163  }
5164 
5165  return TRUE;
5166 }
